reviewText: Not very good. It drags. Had a hard time waiting for it to get good. Never did.

This was a great movie, way more entertaining than i had expected. The characters really draw you into the story, and their interactions keep you captivated throughout. there are funny moments, tense moments, and everything in between. It is overall a very good movie, and very high quality.

"Rolling" is a modern day twist of "The Breakfast Club" giving the world an inside view of what it's like to be a teenager in today's world, dealing with the issues of drugs, peer pressure, sexualities, friendships and more. From its beginning to end, this film is capturing and entertaining with a diverse cast and jaw dropping scandals. "Rolling" is a timeless film that everyone can identify with.
"Rolling" is a modern and fun twist on the "Breakfast Club". It puts its own spin on teenage problems and doesn't shy away from the harsh realities of today's world.
You will definitely want to have this in your collection.  A fun, interesting and surprising story, with a fresh and talented cast.  Hats off to new, independent filmmaker, Damon Jamal.
Rolling is entertaining, dramatic, and sometimes hilarious.  The plot has interesting twists and turns, engaging to the very end.  Camera work is excellent.  Five stars!

the cast, the plot, the directing - all amazing. I don't want to spoil it by getting into details but "Rolling" will definitely have your attention from beginning to end. captivating, fun, and modern. a 5 star film.
